    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>New York,</placeName>
                    <date>25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> July 1879.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I take pleasure in sending you an article of mine, briefly summatory of the main causes of decline in the Hawaiian population.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It contains little or nothing that is new; but it seems to me that the <hi rend="underline">intellectual</hi> perturbation of savages under civilization, as a possible cause of their infertility, has not yet, perhaps, been sufficiently studied.</p>
                    <p>Let me say that I am in frequent correspondence with my father, the Rev. Titus Coan of Hilo, &amp; that he would be happy to answer, either directly or through me, according to the best of his observations, any questions about the Islanders that you might take interest in asking.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Very sincerely yours, | T. M. Coan. <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Dr. Charles Darwin.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Coan sent his article ‘The decay of the Polynesian’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10911.xml">[Coan] 1879</ref>); CD’s copy is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL. </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Coan’s father, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7505.xml">Titus Coan</ref>, was a missionary based at Hilo, Hawaii, since 1835.</note>
        </div>   
       
